cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the application of the Grad-CAM method for deep model prediction in image classification and image captioning, which are primarily computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the challenges of applying Grad-CAM to embedding networks, which are trained using millions of dynamically paired examples, indicating a focus on machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to a house price estimation application using images, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
